1.0: -First public release.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "PenDenTive" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on any tile present on the board, if there is one
tile on top of it and one tile under, those tiles will exchange their
position. If there is only one tile, either over or under the tile you
clicked on, that tile will exchange its position with the one you clicked
on. Of course if there is no tile either under or over the one you
clicked on, nothing will happen.

  If 3 or more tiles of the same type are in line with each other, those
tiles will then be removed from the game board and you will get points
according to the number of tiles in that lineup:

  3 tiles give 1 point
  4 "  "  "  " 10 points
  5 "  "  "  " 100 points

  ...The fun begins when you make more than one alignment of tiles of the
same type, for example: if you make 2 alignments of 3 similar tiles, you
will get 1 point for each alignment, that total will be added and the
result will be multiplied by the number of alignements, in this case:
2 points x 2 aligments = 4 points total... As you can see, the amount
of points earned can go up quite a bit...

  However! If you make alignments of 3 or more tiles of the same type,
and there are tiles located under the tiles you lined up, as the same
type tiles will then be removed, the tiles located under will "fall", as
they will loose their "support", so to speak. Everytime that happens, you
will be penalized in that the gauge located at the right of the game
board will rise according to the amount of "lost" (or fallen) tiles... If
that gauge fills up completely, the game will be over.

  Note that as the gauge is rising, it is normally coloured in blue, if
it gets coloured in red, watch out!... 

  Another thing to watch for: when you click on tiles and no alignment
of at least 3 similar tiles are made, a new tile will appear somewhere
in the lower part of a suspended set of tiles. Do not let the board fill
up completely, because if that happens the game will be over.

  Every time you make an alignment that gives you 100 points or more, the
gauge will lower a little... that is, if you do not let 10 tiles or more
fall towards the bottom of the game board...!

  At the start of every game, 5 different types of tiles will appear on
the game board, as you progress in the game, new types of tiles will
appear...

  The main goal is to make aligments in the lowest parts of the suspended
tiles, as to not lose too much tiles at a time. If you happen to clear
the entire board, and you do not "bust" the lost tiles gauge, your score
will be doubled and the game will end.

  Have fun!

@endnode

